com.mesosfer

Class MesosferPushBroadcastReceiver

  • java.lang.Object
    • android.content.BroadcastReceiver
      • com.mesosfer.MesosferPushBroadcastReceiver

  • public class MesosferPushBroadcastReceiver
extends BroadcastReceiver
    A BroadcastReceiver for rendering and reacting to to Notifications.

    This BroadcastReceiver must be registered in order to use the MesosferPush subscription methods. As a security precaution, the intent filters for this BroadcastReceiver must not be exported. Add the following lines to your AndroidManifest.xml file, inside the <application> element to properly register the MesosferPushBroadcastReceiver: 

     <receiver android:name="com.mesosfer.MesosferPushBroadcastReceiver" android:exported=false>
  <intent-filter>
     <action android:name="com.mesosfer.push.intent.RECEIVE" />
     <action android:name="com.mesosfer.push.intent.OPEN" />
     <action android:name="com.mesosfer.push.intent.DELETE" />
   </intent-filter>
 </receiver>

    The MesosferPushBroadcastReceiver is designed to provide maximal configurability with minimal effort. To customize the push icon, add the following line as a child of your <application> element: 

       <meta-data android:name="com.mesosfer.push.notification_icon"
              android:resource="@drawable/icon"/>

    where drawable/icon may be the path to any drawable resource. The Android style guide for Notifications suggests that push icons should be flat monochromatic images.

    To achieve further customization, MesosferPushBroadcastReceiver can be subclassed. When providing your own implementation of MesosferPushBroadcastReceiver, be sure to change com.mesosfer.PushBroadcastReceiver to the name of your custom subclass in your AndroidManifest.xml. You can intercept and override the behavior of entire portions of the push lifecycle by overriding onPushReceive(Context, Intent), onPushOpen(Context, Intent), or onPushDismiss(Context, Intent). To make minor changes to the appearance of a notification, override getSmallIconId(Context, Intent) or getLargeIcon(Context, Intent). To completely change the Notification generated, override getNotification(Context, Intent). To change the Activity launched when a user opens a Notification, override getActivity(Context, Intent).
